title: Byfuglien scores late as Jets beat Flames 3-1
text: Add a message (optional) Success - Article sent! close Winnipeg Jets' Nikolaj Ehlers (27), left to right, Mark Scheifele (55), Dustin Byfuglien (33), Toby Enstrom (39) and Mathieu Perreault (85) celebrate Byfuglien's goal against the Calgary Flames during the third period of an NHL hockey game, Friday Oct. 16, 2015 in Winnipeg, Manitoba. (John Woods/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT Associated Press Winnipeg Jets' Dustin Byfuglien's, left, celebrates his goal as Calgary Flames' Sean Monahan (23) and John Gaudreau, right, look on during the third period of an NHL hockey game, Friday Oct. 16, 2015 in Winnipeg, Manitoba. (John Woods/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT Associated Press Calgary Flames' goaltender Karri Ramo, right, stops a shot as Winnipeg Jets' Nic Petan, left, looks for the rebound during second-period NHL hockey game action in Winnipeg, Manitoba, Friday, Oct. 16, 2015. (John Woods/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT Associated Press Calgary Flames' Mason Raymond, left, (21) leaps over Winnipeg Jets' Tyler Myers (57) as goaltender Ondrej Pavelec (31) saves his shot during the third period of an NHL hockey game, Friday Oct. 16, 2015 in Winnipeg, Manitoba. (John Woods/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT Associated Press Winnipeg Jets' Bryan Little, centre, celebrates his goal with teammate Blake Wheeler (26) against Calgary Flames' goaltender Karri Ramo (31) and Dennis Wideman, left, during the second period of an NHL hockey game, Friday Oct. 16, 2015 in Winnipeg, Manitoba. (John Woods/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT Associated Press Calgary Flames' Mikael Backlund, (11) Sean Monahan (23) and Michael Frolik (67) celebrate Backlund's goal as Winnipeg Jets' Blake Wheeler, left, skates by during the first period of an NHL hockey game, Friday Oct. 16, 2015 in Winnipeg, Manitoba. (John Woods/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT Associated Press Calgary Flames' Michael Ferland, right, attempts the deflection past Winnipeg Jets' goaltender Ondrej Pavelec (31) as Adam Pardy (2) and Tyler Myers (57) look on during the first period of an NHL hockey game, Friday Oct. 16, 2015 in Winnipeg, Manitoba. (John Woods/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT Associated Press
